did.head: Collection Summary

repository.corpname: Woodson Research Center, Rice University, Houston, Texas

did.abstract: The papers of Dickson Fagan (1903-1977), Austin, Texas attorney active in the Democratic Party, include correspondence with both state and national political figures as well as Fagan's personal and business subject files clippings, published materials and notes, dating from 1950-1978.

bioghist.head: Biographical Note
bioghist.p: Austin, Texas attorney (1903-1977) active in the Democratic Party.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Papers include correspondence with both state and national political figures as well as Fagan's personal and business subject files of clippings, published materials, and notes, 1950-1978.

Correspondents include Dickson, James F.; Bentsen, Lloyd; Briscoe, Dolph; Buckley, William F. Jr.; Cranston, Alan; Carter, Jimmy ; Domenici, Pete V.; Dugger, Ronnie; Fullbright J.W.; Ford, Gerald; Faulk, John Henry; Johnson, Lyndon B.; Jordan, Barbara; Kissinger, Henry; McCarthy, Eugene; McGovern, George; Maverick, Maury, Jr.; Moos, Malcom; Mondale, Walter F.; Moyers, Bill; Muskie, Edmund; Nixon, Richard M.; Pickle, J.J. (Jake); Richards, Ann; Thurmond, Strom; Weddington, Sarah; and others.

accessrestrict.head: Access Restrictions
accessrestrict.p: This material is open for research. Stored off-site at the Library Service Center. Please request this material via woodson@rice.edu or call 713-348-2586.

acqinfo.head: Acquisition Information
acqinfo.p: Gift of W. Hall via Ellis Rudy, 1978.
Formerly part of W. Hall papers - contact WRC staff for further information.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Fagan Dickson Papers, 1950-1978, MS 281, Woodson Research Center, Fondren Library, Rice University

userestrict.head: Use Restrictions
userestrict.p: Permission to publish material from the Fagan Dickson Papers must be obtained from the Woodson Research Center, Fondren Library.
